<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>lufact  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="luget"> extraction of sparse LU factors  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[P,L,U,Q]=luget(hand)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>hand  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : handle, output of <VERB>lufact</VERB>
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>P  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : sparse permutation matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>L  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : sparse matrix, lower triangular if <VERB>hand</VERB> is obtained from a  non singular matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>U  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : square non singular upper triangular sparse matrix with ones along the main diagonal
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>Q  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : sparse permutation matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    <VERB>[P,L,U,Q]=luget(hand)</VERB> with <VERB>hand</VERB> obtained by
    the command <VERB>[hand,rk]=lufact(A)</VERB> with <VERB>A</VERB> a sparse matrix
    returns four sparse matrices such that <VERB>P*L*U*Q=A</VERB>.
  </P>
  <P>
    The A matrix needs not be full rank but must be square 
    (since A is assumed sparse one may add zeros if necessary to squaring
    down A).
  </P>
  <P>
    If <VERB>A</VERB> is singular, the <VERB>L</VERB> matrix is column compressed (with
    <VERB>rk</VERB> independent nonzero columns):  the nonsingular sparse 
    matrix <VERB>Q&apos;*inv(U)</VERB> column compresses <VERB>A</VERB>.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
a=rand(5,2)*rand(2,5);A=sparse(a);
[hand,rk]=lufact(A);[P,L,U,Q]=luget(hand);
full(L), P*L*U*Q-A
clean(P*L*U*Q-A)
ludel(hand)
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
